<doc>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_CONFIGURATION">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines the gestures that can be passed to <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/windows/desktop/api/directmanipulation/nf-directmanipulation-idirectmanipulationviewport-setmanualgesture">SetManualGesture</a>.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>By default, <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/windows/desktop/directmanipulation/direct-manipulation-portal">Direct Manipulation</a> always reassigns tap and press-and-hold gestures to the application.</para>
      <para>Use <b>DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_PINCH_ZOOM</b> to zoom instead of scale.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/windows/desktop/directmanipulation/direct-manipulation-enumerations">Direct Manipulation Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_CONFIGURATION.DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>No gestures are defined.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_CONFIGURATION.DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_DEFAULT">
    <summary>
      <para>Only default gestures are supported. This is the default value.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_CONFIGURATION.DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_CROSS_SLIDE_VERTICAL">
    <summary>
      <para>Vertical slide and swipe gestures are supported through the cross-slide interaction. For more information, see <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/uwp/input-and-devices/guidelines-for-cross-slide">Guidelines for cross-slide</a>.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_CONFIGURATION.DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_CROSS_SLIDE_HORIZONTAL">
    <summary>
      <para>Horizontal slide and swipe gestures are supported through the cross-slide interaction. For more information, see <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/uwp/input-and-devices/guidelines-for-cross-slide">Guidelines for cross-slide</a>.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_CONFIGURATION.DIRECTMANIPULATION_GESTURE_PINCH_ZOOM">
    <summary>
      <para>Pinch and stretch gestures for zooming.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>